      "paragraph_name": "COPAU0AI",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This data structure defines the layout for input and output data related to a screen or transaction. It includes fields for transaction name (TRNNAMEL, TRNNAMEF, TRNNAMEA, TRNNAMEI), title (TITLE01L, TITLE01F, TITLE01A, TITLE01I), and current date (CURDATEL, CURDATEF). The 'L' fields likely represent the length of the associated data, 'F' fields are single-character flags, 'A' fields are single-character redefinitions of the flag fields, and 'I' fields contain the actual data. The structure also includes filler fields for spacing and alignment. This copybook is likely used by a CICS program to format data for display on a screen and to receive input from the user.",
